LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
HOUSE BILL NO. 141
BY EDUCATION COMMITTEE
1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO EDUCATION; PROVIDING LEGISLATIVE FINDINGS AND INTENT; AMEND-
3 ING CHAPTER 37, TITLE 33, IDAHO CODE, BY THE ADDITION OF A NEW SECTION
4 33-3732, IDAHO CODE, TO ESTABLISH PROVISIONS REGARDING TITLE IX COMPLI-
5 ANCE IN HIGHER EDUCATION; AND DECLARING AN EMERGENCY AND PROVIDING AN
6 EFFECTIVE DATE.
7 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
8 SECTION 1. LEGISLATIVE FINDINGS AND INTENT. The Legislature finds that
9 direct accountability is necessary and appropriate to ensure that institu-
10 tions of higher education in the state of Idaho effectively implement the
11 provisions of Title IX of the Education Amendments of 1972 (20 U.S.C. 1681
12 et seq.). Accordingly, it is the intent of the Legislature to assign sole re-
13 sponsibility for Title IX compliance to the president of each public insti-
14 tution of higher education in the state of Idaho to ensure that Title IX re-
15 sponsibilities are implemented, overseen, and enforced at the highest level
16 of leadership within each institution.
17 SECTION 2. That Chapter 37, Title 33, Idaho Code, be, and the same is
18 hereby amended by the addition thereto of a NEW SECTION, to be known and des-
19 ignated as Section 33-3732, Idaho Code, and to read as follows:
20 33-3732. TITLE IX COMPLIANCE IN HIGHER EDUCATION. (1) For the purposes
21 of this section:
22 (a) "Institution of higher education" means any public postsecondary
23 institution, including but not limited to universities, colleges, and
24 community colleges, operating within the state of Idaho that receives
25 federal financial assistance.
26 (b) "Office for civil rights" means the federal agency responsible for
27 enforcing title IX compliance within educational institutions.
28 (c) "President" means the chief executive officer or equivalent high-
29 est-ranking official of an institution of higher education in the state
30 of Idaho, without regard to the specific title of such individual.
31 (d) "Title IX" means title IX of the education amendments of 1972 (20
32 U.S.C. 1681 et seq.), and all applicable federal regulations duly pro-
33 mulgated by any federal department or agency pursuant to the same.
34 (e) "Title IX compliance" means the policies, procedures, actions, and
35 investigations required by title IX to ensure that an institution of
36 higher education is in compliance with title IX.
37 (2) The president of each institution of higher education in Idaho
38 shall have the exclusive authority and duty to implement all title IX compli-
39 ance. When necessary, the president of an institution of higher education
40 may delegate specific tasks or duties related to title IX to designated staff
41 within the office of the president, provided that the president approves any

2
1 final decision or action on any title IX related task or duty. To carry out
2 this provision, the president of each institution of higher education in
3 Idaho shall:
4 (a) Establish policies to implement the requirements of title IX and
5 corresponding binding federal regulations issued by the United States
6 department of education and the office for civil rights. Such policies
7 shall be narrowly tailored to meet only the minimum requirements of ti-
8 tle IX; and
9 (b) Ensure that all complaints filed with the institution of higher
10 education pursuant to title IX are promptly investigated in accordance
11 with title IX regulations. The president shall review and approve any
12 decisions regarding sanctions, accommodations, or disciplinary ac-
13 tions arising from title IX complaints.
14 (3) The president of each institution of higher education shall pre-
15 pare and submit a report to the Idaho state board of education and the Idaho
16 legislative services office no later than July 1 of each year, which report
17 shall include:
18 (a) The number of title IX complaints received during the previous aca-
19 demic year. The report shall also include the number of investigations
20 conducted and a description of the outcomes of all investigations;
21 (b) Copies of all title IX-related policies and procedures of the in-
22 stitution of higher education, which shall conspicuously highlight any
23 changes made to such policies and procedures during the previous year;
24 (c) A summary of interim measures taken to protect complainants and the
25 accused during the time an investigation is pending; and
26 (d) A summary of all corrective actions taken to address failures in ti-
27 tle IX compliance.
28 SECTION 3. An emergency existing therefor, which emergency is hereby
29 declared to exist, this act shall be in full force and effect on and after
30 July 1, 2025.

